{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nA work ticket carries a single attestation slot (`state[\"signature\"]`), written\nlast-writer-wins by `process_signature` (`src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py`). The\nplan-review attestation (claim time) and the completion verdict (close time) share that\nslot, so closing destroys the plan-review attestation (bug grumpy-site-beard /\ne6a0-ba9b-ae92-43d7). The two are independent proofs and must coexist; we also expect\nfurther attestation kinds and per-ticket CI-gate consumption later.\n\n## What\nAdd `state[\"attestations\"]`, a map keyed by attestation kind (per-key LWW, mirroring\n`process_workflow_run`): additive across kinds, latest within a kind. Kind is derived from\nthe already-signed `manifest[0]` (`plan-review` / `completion-verifier`), so no\n`PAYLOAD_VERSION` bump and existing signatures still verify. Reuse the `SIGNATURE` event\n(add an unsigned `data[\"kind\"]` ONLY as a routing hint). Attestations are immutable signed\nrecords; validity for a gate is computed on read via one\n`compute_validity(attestation, ticket_state, kind)` dispatcher.\n\n## Kind identity + routing\n- The SIGNED `manifest[0]` is AUTHORITATIVE for kind. Parse: the substring before the first\n  \":\" (e.g. \"plan-review: PASS\" -> \"plan-review\").\n- `data[\"kind\"]` is only a hint; `process_signature` uses it ONLY if it equals the\n  manifest-derived kind, else ignores it (never trust the unsigned envelope over the signed\n  manifest). A SIGNATURE event whose manifest is empty/unkindable (e.g. a legacy retired\n  blank event) is ignored for routing (cannot key it) — its staleness is now handled by\n  validity-on-read, not by clobbering.\n\n## Compiled-state shape + the legacy mirror\n- `process_signature` writes BOTH `state[\"attestations\"][kind] = record` AND keeps\n  `state[\"signature\"]` as a LIVE mirror of the MOST-RECENT attestation (last SIGNATURE\n  event wins the mirror), in live compiled state — not only in SNAPSHOT output.\n- Why the live mirror: four existing consumers read `state.get(\"signature\")` directly\n  (`signing.verify_signature`, the close-gate path, `fsck`/validate, and the\n  soon-removed `retire_attested_pin`); the live mirror means they keep working unchanged\n  while `attestations` is wired up, AND it makes the SNAPSHOT/rollback mirror automatic\n  (compiled_state already carries `signature`). The record shape is unchanged\n  (manifest, algorithm, signature, key_id, head_sha, signed_at, author).\n- 114f owns the canonical per-record shape; 2c2d/cc1b/ed26 reference it.\n\n## Migration (expand only; contract deferred) + rollback\n- Events keep the UNCHANGED `SIGNATURE` shape (plus the optional hint `data[\"kind\"]`),\n  so old code replays them fine.\n- Read fold-in: an OLD SNAPSHOT whose `compiled_state` carries only `signature` (no\n  `attestations`) is folded into `attestations` on restore (kind from its manifest).\n  Raw post-snapshot SIGNATURE events replay normally into the map.\n- New SNAPSHOTs carry BOTH `attestations` and the `signature` mirror automatically (the\n  reducer maintains the mirror), so a rolled-back / not-yet-upgraded clone still reads one\n  attestation. ROLLBACK is therefore safe at any time.\n- The \"contract\" phase (dropping the mirror) is OUT OF SCOPE here; tracked by follow-up\n  352b-5097-9971-4dc1, gated on an all-clones-upgraded readiness check.\n\n## Verification surface\n- `verify_signature(ticket_id, kind=\"plan-review\")` ALWAYS returns a SINGLE verdict dict;\n  `verify_signature_result.schema.json` is UNCHANGED. `kind` defaults to `\"plan-review\"`,\n  so every existing library/MCP/CLI caller that omits a kind keeps single-verdict\n  back-compat. Internally it reads `state[\"attestations\"][kind]`, falling back to the\n  legacy `state[\"signature\"]` when the map is absent.\n- The verify-ALL map is a SEPARATE entry-point `verify_attestations(ticket_id) ->\n  {kind: verdict}` (NOT a new return shape of `verify_signature`).\n- CLI: `verify-signature <t> --kind K` = single-gate exit code (0 iff certified);\n  `verify-signature <t>` (no `--kind`) = human-readable listing via `verify_attestations`\n  (exit 0 iff all certified). MCP `verify_signature` stays single (kind defaults to\n  plan-review); the full per-kind set is surfaced via `show`/ticket-state (ed26) — no MCP\n  schema break.\n- Callers migrated to pass an explicit kind: `claim_gate_check`, `drift_refresh_candidate`,\n  `refresh_attestation` (attest.py) -> `plan-review`; `_child_closure_findings`\n  (completion.py) -> `completion-verifier`.\n\n## Validity model (computed on read; records never mutated)\n- `compute_validity(attestation, ticket_state, kind)` centralizes per-kind rules; the\n  MATERIAL-CHANGE field set reuses the EXISTING plan-review material fingerprint\n  (`orchestrator.material_fingerprint`: description/AC/file_impact/children) as the single\n  source — no new separately-owned constant. \"Computed on read\" means NOT stored/mutated;\n  it MAY do I/O (plan-review still performs its filesystem code-drift re-hash).\n- DATA SOURCE for \"not reopened since\": the reducer records `state[\"last_reopened_at\"]` =\n  the timestamp of the most recent `closed -> open` transition (detected in `process_status`\n  from the pre-update status == \"closed\" and target == \"open\"); null if never reopened.\n  `compute_validity` checks `signed_at >= last_reopened_at` (or null) purely from compiled\n  state.\n- completion-verifier valid iff: certified AND status==\"closed\" AND not-reopened-since AND\n  material-fingerprint-unchanged-since `signed_at` (the completion signer records the\n  material fingerprint in its manifest, symmetric with plan-review).\n- plan-review valid iff: existing freshness (material + filesystem code drift) AND\n  not-reopened-since.\n- `retire_attested_pin` (the blank-`SIGNATURE`-on-reopen mutation, signing.py) is REMOVED\n  with its reopen call (transition.py); reopen invalidation is validity-on-read for both\n  kinds. No lifecycle transition mutates any attestation record.\n\n## Presentation (no secret leak)\n- `public_state()` (`_present.py`) gets a DEDICATED `attestations` branch (the flat\n  `_INTERNAL_SUBKEYS` cannot express a wildcard kind level): if `out[\"attestations\"]` is a\n  dict, replace with `{kind: {k:v for k,v in rec.items() if k != \"signature\"} for kind, rec\n  in out[\"attestations\"].items() if isinstance(rec, dict)}`. The legacy single-`signature`\n  one-level hex strip is retained. This is the canonical strip path for all present/future\n  kinds.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- A ticket simultaneously holds plan-review AND completion attestations; signing one never\n  clobbers the other (in `attestations`); re-running a kind replaces only that kind.\n- Compaction/SNAPSHOT round-trips all kinds; legacy single-signature tickets and old-clone\n  snapshots still read/verify; a new snapshot is readable by old code via the mirror.\n- A reopened ticket stops reading as completion-valid AND plan-review-valid (via\n  validity-on-read) with no record mutation; re-closing/re-reviewing re-signs the kind.\n- No HMAC hex appears in `show`/MCP output for any attestation kind.\n\n## Validation\n- Manual dogfood smoke-test: create a ticket, sign a plan-review PASS, sign a\n  completion-verifier PASS, `rebar show` shows BOTH kinds (neither overwriting the other,\n  no hex); reopen and confirm both read not-valid; `rebar verify-signature --kind K` per\n  kind.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `state[\"attestations\"]` (kind-keyed, per-key LWW) added; `process_signature` writes\n      `attestations[kind]` AND maintains the live `state[\"signature\"]` most-recent mirror;\n      routing uses authoritative `manifest[0]` (data[\"kind\"] only as a validated hint).\n- [ ] Signed canonical payload unchanged; every pre-existing signature still certifies.\n- [ ] Old-snapshot read fold-in (`signature` -> `attestations`); new SNAPSHOTs carry both\n      `attestations` and the mirror; contract deferred to 352b.\n- [ ] Reducer records `state[\"last_reopened_at\"]` (most recent closed->open; null if never).\n- [ ] `compute_validity(attestation, ticket_state, kind)` centralizes per-kind validity,\n      reusing the existing material fingerprint; completion = certified AND closed AND\n      not-reopened-since AND material-unchanged-since; plan-review = existing freshness AND\n      not-reopened-since.\n- [ ] `retire_attested_pin` removed; no transition mutates any attestation record.\n- [ ] `verify_signature(ticket_id, kind=\"plan-review\")` returns a single verdict (schema\n      unchanged, back-compat default); `verify_attestations(ticket_id)` returns\n      `{kind: verdict}`; CLI no-`--kind` lists all (exit 0 iff all certified); claim gate\n      reads `plan-review`, close + child-closure read `completion-verifier`.\n- [ ] `public_state()` dedicated `attestations` branch strips the `signature` subkey from\n      every per-kind record (no hex in show/MCP for any kind); legacy strip retained.\n- [ ] `show`/MCP render the `attestations` map (omitted when empty).\n- [ ] Tests: coexistence; within-kind replace; compaction round-trip; legacy + new-snapshot\n      cross-read; reopen invalidates completion + plan-review validity without mutation;\n      material-change invalidates completion; concurrent different-kind signs both survive;\n      no HMAC hex in public output.\n## compute_validity contract (pinned)\n`compute_validity(attestation, ticket_state, kind, *, repo_root=None) -> {\"valid\": bool,\n\"reason\": str}`. It ASSUMES the attestation record is already HMAC-certified (the caller\nruns `verify_signature` first); compute_validity adds ONLY the lifecycle/freshness layer on\ntop (per-kind: completion = closed AND not-reopened-since AND material-unchanged-since;\nplan-review = material + filesystem code-drift AND not-reopened-since). `reason` is a\nhuman-readable explanation when `valid` is False (empty/\"certified ...\" when True).\nConsumers: `claim_gate_check` (plan-review), the close gate + `_child_closure_findings`\n(completion-verifier) call it and branch on `.valid`.\n## Acceptance Criteria (compute_validity)\n- [ ] `compute_validity(...)` returns `{\"valid\": bool, \"reason\": str}`; callers HMAC-verify first then branch on `.valid`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782795026624523001,"uuid":"3b75bd6f-0813-43cb-b672-54c27788a0a2"}